{
  {{- /*
    pi keybindings — https://pi.dev/docs/latest/keybindings (docs/keybindings.md)

    Three intents captured here:

    1. Submit / newline. Enter inserts a newline; submit with Ctrl+Enter
       (Ctrl+J kept as a fallback — it emits a distinct line-feed byte and so
       works as submit in terminals that don't speak the kitty keyboard
       protocol, where Enter / Shift+Enter / Ctrl+Enter are otherwise
       indistinguishable).

    2. Keep standard Emacs/readline editing chords intact in the prompt. Pi
       binds the readline set by default (Ctrl+A/E/B/F/K/U/W/Y, Alt+B/F/D/Y,
       Ctrl+D, Ctrl+-) but several app actions are hoisted onto the main editor
       and shadow editing chords. Free them so Ctrl/Alt+letter editing keys
       behave as an Emacs/readline user expects, and move pi's app commands to
       the Alt namespace:
         - Ctrl+P / Ctrl+N      -> cursor up / down (were: model cycle / unbound)
         - Alt+Left / Alt+Right -> model cycle prev / next (off Ctrl+P; Alt
           rather than Ctrl+arrow because macOS Mission Control eats Ctrl+arrow)
         - Alt+M                -> model select (was Ctrl+L = clear-screen)
         - Ctrl+T and Ctrl+G unbound — app.thinking.toggle (transpose-chars)
           and app.editor.external (abort/keyboard-quit) removed from those
           chords; reach them via menu / slash commands.
       Word movement keeps Alt+B / Alt+F (and Ctrl+Left / Ctrl+Right). Ctrl+D
       stays app.exit but pi gates it to an empty buffer, so delete-char-forward
       is preserved while typing. These bindings also apply inside pi-vimmode's
       INSERT mode, which delegates editing keys to pi's native editor (see
       settings.json `packages`).

    3. Ctrl+[ is another escape route for cancellation. Modern terminals report
       it distinctly through CSI-u, so bind it alongside physical Escape for
       interruption and selectors without remapping raw terminal input.

    Rendered as a chezmoi template purely so this rationale survives as a comment;
    the emitted file is plain JSON (pi rejects non-keybinding keys like "_comment").
  */ -}}
  "tui.input.newLine": ["enter", "shift+enter"],
  "tui.input.submit": ["ctrl+enter", "ctrl+j"],
  "app.interrupt": ["escape", "ctrl+["],
  "tui.select.cancel": ["escape", "ctrl+c", "ctrl+["],
  "tui.editor.cursorUp": ["up", "ctrl+p"],
  "tui.editor.cursorDown": ["down", "ctrl+n"],
  "app.model.cycleForward": ["alt+right"],
  "app.model.cycleBackward": ["alt+left"],
  "app.model.select": ["alt+m"],
  "app.thinking.toggle": [],
  "app.editor.external": []
}
